Type any one of the following command to find os name and version in Linux:
cat /etc/os-release
lsb_release -a
hostnamectl

Type the following command to find Linux kernel version:
uname -r

change time zone in debian


timedatectl

ls -l /etc/localtime

timedatectl list-timezones



sudo timedatectl set-timezone Asia/Kolkata

sudo rm -f /etc/localtime

sudo ln -s /usr/share/zoneinfo/Asia/Kolkata /etc/localtime

Mysql Timezone change
SELECT @@global.time_zone, @@session.time_zone;
SET GLOBAL time_zone = '+5:30';
select now();


#check free and used space ubuntu
df -h
df -h --total

Ram infomation
Run the following command to see RAM information in KiB (1 Kibibyte is 1024 bytes).

free

Run the following command to see RAM information in MiB (1 Mebibyte is 1,048,576 bytes).

free -m

Run the following command to see RAM information in GiB (1 Gibibyte is 1,073,741,824 bytes).

free -g
